        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(infra): bound jsonl-socket response buffer to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`requestJsonlSocket` accumulates incoming socket data into a string buffer until a newline is seen or the socket closes. A buggy or hostile peer that streams data without newlines can force the runtime to keep buffering until timeout or OOM.\n\nThis PR bounds that pending JSONL line buffer in the shared requester. It intentionally stays infra-only and does not change macOS exec-host producer output semantics.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts`\n  - Adds `JSONL_SOCKET_MAX_BUFFER_BYTES = 16 * 1024 * 1024`.\n  - Returns `null` and destroys the socket once the pending line buffer exceeds the cap.\n  - Exposes the cap through `testApi` so tests stay aligned with the production limit.\n- `src/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts`\n  - Adds a regression test for an oversized newline-free socket response.\n  - Streams chunks over the real socket until the production cap is exceeded and handles the expected server-side EPIPE after the requester destroys the socket.\n  - Asserts the result arrives before the timeout window, so the test proves the cap path instead of the existing timeout path.\n\n## Current status proof\n\n- **Current head**: `2da595da9d5fe957ab5d43e2f762339456ad6c75`.\n- **Current GitHub PR diff**: `+51/-1 (2 files)`.\n- **Current changed files**:\n\n```text\nsrc/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts\nsrc/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n```\n\nThe previous macOS exec-host producer changes were removed from the final PR diff. This PR now only changes the shared JSONL requester and its focused regression test.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: A peer streaming a newline-free body larger than the cap must not hang or grow memory until timeout; the call must return `null` quickly.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Node v22 workspace, real `net.createServer` / `net.Socket` over a Unix domain socket in `/tmp`.\n- **Exact steps**: `node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts` starts a server that streams 64 KiB chunks every 5 ms with no newline, then calls `requestJsonlSocket` with a 2 s timeout.\n- **Observed result after fix**: `RESULT: result=null elapsedMs=104`.\n- **Negative control on current main**: `RESULT: result=null elapsedMs=2016`.\n\n## Compatibility note\n\n`requestJsonlSocket` is shared by exec-host and exec-approval socket requests. This PR intentionally uses a 16 MiB requester-side fail-closed cap but does not define a macOS exec-host stdout/stderr truncation contract. If maintainers want a producer-side exec-host output budget, that should be a separate owner-reviewed PR.\n\nThe merge decision for this infra-only PR is therefore whether maintainers accept a 16 MiB shared JSONL response budget for the requester guard.\n\n## Evidence\n\nTerminal proof (real socket, streaming peer without newlines):\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts\nRESULT: result=null elapsedMs=104\n```\n\nNegative control (temporary revert to `origin/main`):\n\n```text\n$ git checkout origin/main -- src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts\nRESULT: result=null elapsedMs=2016\n$ git checkout HEAD -- src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n```\n\nFocused Vitest after restoring infra-only scope:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts --run\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  6 passed (6)\n```\n\nThe oversized-buffer regression uses a 500 ms timeout and asserts the result returns in under 250 ms, so current main's timeout-only behavior would not satisfy the test.\n\nWhitespace/check sanity after restoring infra-only scope:\n\n```text\n$ git diff --check\n# exit 0\n```\n\nEarlier type checks on this PR:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm tsgo:core      # exit 0\n$ pnpm tsgo:core:test # exit 0\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix/jsonl-socket-buffer-bound",
